"(1) (i) ’s boots echoed through the steel corridors of the Phobos Base’s lower maintenance levels as sirens shrieked through her earpiece. The air shimmered with the acrid tang of superheated plasma, and red emergency lights strobed in erratic pulses across the bulkheads. She was just passing the access hatch to Reactor Bay 7 when the ground beneath her shuddered—a deep, resonant groan that vibrated up through her spine. Her breath caught as she saw the wall of light erupt behind the reinforced glass, the fusion core’s containment field fracturing in a violent cascade of golden-white fire. Instinctively, she ducked behind a console as the pressure wave slammed into the bulkhead, metal buckling with a scream that was half thunder, half agony. Lillian Mendoza. witnessed a fusion core breach.\n(2) (i) Through the crack in the failing wall, Lillian could see the reactor chamber itself: swirling vortices of light, fragments of plasma arcing like living lightning, and the desperate faces of engineers $entity_1 and $entity_2 scrambling to seal the breach with magnetic clamps. The base’s gravity systems flickered, alarms blared in a rising crescendo, and the smell of ozone and burning superconductor filled the air. Lillian’s heart hammered against her suit as she realized the breach was accelerating, the core’s instability spreading like wildfire. Every second, the future of the base—and everyone inside—hung in the balance. Phobos Military Base. September 13, 2225."